          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used for private or public recitation, prayer and worship (pūjā) in praise of the Hindu goddess Gaṅgā known also as the river Ganges especially in the city of Vāraṇasī, sacred to the Hindu religion. Frequent mention of Śiva. Title translates as the Wave of the Ganges. Work is incomplete. Includes part of an unidentified commentary. A second fragment of a text from the Anusmṛti dedicated to Viṣṇu is at the end (f. 15).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
